			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Few things....
<br />

<br />
1. The Shared Death idea, I think, is foolish.  Yes, I know that Healers can die for healing too much... or a Nuker can die for over nuking... but that is not my fault they did that.  Seeing that I have little control on how they play, the group then must hope they do not botch it.  This part I can see, mistakes happen.  So that is fine but then there are the, "Pick UP groups from Hell"  that are not fun or in time unavoidable.  Also this can bring up issues of Griefing. LDs and other tactics to cause others to die.  You do not see it yet... you will see it in Open BETA or Launch.
<br />
A player joins and just plays bad out of spite, goes AFK and we pay for their foolishness, grieffing, or in blunt terms, stupidness? 
<br />
Untill I play and see how this is, I am not in favor for this.  Too many times I have joined a pickup group only to have it be ONE BAD experience... or death, after death, after death... early days of BoThunder/TAC??  Not because the spot was too hard or wrong classes.  But due to players not knowing how to play their class, ebay fools, LDers, lazy AFKers, someone not watching what they are doing.... a standard "bad" Pickup group.
<br />
I see this as pushing some to Solo more vs grouping up with Unknowns or undesirables.  Only if this turns into an issue in the end game and EXP loss on death is like EQLive loss... where a few deaths could just ruin your whole afternoon, day or even week.
<br />
Then the other issue, agro range in EQLive always was bad... and in some spots, you had no choice but to "eat a death"  not because of poor play but because you lagged a bit, server spiked and you bounced into a wall...  now players are going to be punished if someone has a bad connection or if someone MUST go AFK and then gets killed for any number of reasons.... Out of game influence does happen... death from that influence has happened... now all will pay for it.  
<br />
Death is bad enough on a solo/single persons experience... now you toss in group-shared penalties.... joy.  
<br />
I can say this, I will disband from a group as often as I can now.  Mainly on getting to point A and point B of exping/raiding or what not.  Yes, I know you can not disband in an instance. 
<br />

<br />
2. Will Shares be easier to get to?  Saying, will we have a way to trace back to them?  Because they are Soul linked... our Death Shard, I hope we can have means of finding them easier.  Not just run blindly to Hide and Seek them.  
<br />

<br />
3. What about Consent?  The life of an EQLive Rogue, I never cared in doing corpse draggings... however, in some spots that was one of the only ways to get to a corpse... was to drag it away from harms way.
<br />
Seeing that you do not release, you can be ressed on the spot... well on the spot, could be under the foot of a Badass mob.
<br />
So how is this going to effect someone who don't want to run all the way back... or leave another shard on the ground...
<br />

<br />
3B.  Can shards be consented?  Picked up by others in order to return to the "owner".
<br />
Mainly falls under the same reasons of #3 Consent.
<br />

<br />
4. How far can an item degrade to from death(s)? To the breaking point, so a death could destroy an item?  
<br />

<br />

<br />
I understand and know there needs to be some form of Risk and Reward...  Just that I do not want to Risk my EXP for a Reward, I earned.   Some classes were designed to stay off the radar of Agro Lists and are able to manage their agro better... now it don't matter what roll you take if you get a overly hyper Nuker or a lacking Healer or a lazy Taunter... the player that don't draw agro, don't die or don't screw up,  will be docked EXP for those that do.  So what is the best Soloing class again?</span><!-- SIG HERE --><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
