				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I do not think it is bad as to cancel the pre-order but I feel it will make the grouping aspect that SoE is going for, harder to pull off.
<br />

<br />
Players that slack now, will be a pain to the group as a whole... not to one person alone.  I could deal with "helping" someone new, but being taxed Debt.  In City of Heroes, they did a debt system...  in some cases it was crazy.  I was level 27 and needed about 200k EXP to level... I died to;
<br />
 
<br />
1: my fault
<br />
3: poor healer.  Fool used a power that targets MOBs to rez fallen, however, seeing he did not know his class, it also drew agro.  In turn killed us before we could react...
<br />
2: For just poor level desgin... pull and before you react, your dead.
<br />

<br />
Total 6 deaths = about 50k debt
<br />

<br />
Now how this system worked, when you gain EXP, half goes to paying off your debt and other goes to your EXP pool.... 
<br />
Now the MOBs average exp, on a solo kill was 50 to 100.  Then in a group 30-80 on normal, no debt to pay off exp.  At the rate I was going, it would have taken me about 2-3 hours of hard soloing... or  about 2 hours of party exping to get out of debt... and saying I did not die again.  This was such a turn off.. it drove me from the character and then the game.
<br />

